      "label": "Procedure",
      "position": {
        "x": 1220,
        "y": 960
      },
      "width": 360,
      "height": 250,
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "title": "Resolve Surfaces In Order",
        "body": "Prefer an explicit source node first, then a dedicated primitive or requested stable role, and only then a generic ui-view-classed port fallback when the contract explicitly allows it. For graph roots, validate minimum surfaces before fallback.",
        "steps": [
          "If a consumer names a source node, use it.",
          "Otherwise, resolve a dedicated primitive such as port-view, icon-view, document-view, or editor-view.",
          "For graph roots, require port and icon surfaces before treating the artifact as fully renderable across zoom.",
          "For planning or status artifacts, require a document surface in addition to port and icon.",
          "Only fall back to a generic ui-view-classed port when the contract explicitly allows it and the role is still unambiguous.",
          "If no role matches, fail or fall back only where the contract explicitly allows it.",
          "Never upgrade a view into bridge authority."
        ],
        "_classBinding": {
          "key": "procedure",
